<article>
    <h2>How to customize ?</h2>
    <p>The default <a href="/avatar">/avatar</a> URL generates a new, randomly generated character every time.</p>
    <p>To customize the generated character, add extra parameters to the URL:</p>
    <p>Example: <a href="/avatar?skinTone=yellow&hair=long">/avatar?skinTone=yellow&hair=long</a></p>
    <p>The URL accepts most of Beanheds properties as parameters. See to the <a
        href="https://github.com/RobertBroersma/beanheads?tab=readme-ov-file#props">full list of Beanheads properties</a>
        on Github.</p>
    <p>To test the effect of each parameter, you can try the <a 
        href="https://beanheads.robertbroersma.com/editor/">BeanHeads Editor</a>.</p>

    <h2>How does it work ?</h2>
    <p><a href="https://beanheads.robertbroersma.com/">BeanHeads</a> is a cool React component by RobertBroersma,
        that generates customizable avatars using SVG, React &amp; Javascript.</p>
    <p>This website is a wrapper around BeanHeads, that makes the component content available without
        React or Javascript.</p>
    
    <p>The <a href="https://github.com/yvzn/beanheads-api">source code is available on Github</a>.</p>
